[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]time student—the facts, I suppose, of the system.  
[normal]For different reasons I would neither encourage nor discourage people from choosing to study somewhere because of finances; for instance, no, you should not go to university just because it is a good financial deal if what you want to do is go and study a vocational course in a college, but, no, you should not be stopped from going to university or choosing which university you want to study at based on a financial decision.  I think there is still confusion about that.  
