[normal]Q76 [bold]&#xa0; 
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] Let us do it for the fun of it; it is so enjoyable, Mr Chairman.  To Bahram, my main question is: you have studied the Government’s model in some detail.  Can you outline the main differences between the Government’s in-house model, which they created, and the one they paid Deloitte £400,000 for? 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Bahram Bekhradnia[bold]: I cannot; I am sorry.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Mr Binley:[bold] Can somebody?  I knew this would be fun.
[normal]&#xa0;
